      <div xml:id="NA245-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kuṟai nērnta tōḻi talaimakaḷai mukampukkatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante who had granted [HIS] request sought the favour of HER.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA245">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nakaiyā kiṉṟē tōḻi takaiya</l>
<l>            vaṇimalar muṇṭakat tāypūṅ kōtai</l>
<l>            maṇimaru ḷaimpāl vaṇṭupaṭat taiit</l>
<l>            tuṇinīrp pauvan tuṇaiyō ṭāṭi</l>
<l>            yoḻukunuṇ ṇucuppi ṉakaṉṟa valkuṟ </l>
<l>            ṟeḷitīṅ kiḷavi yārai yōveṉ</l>
<l>            ṉaritupuṇa riṉṉuyir vauviya nīyeṉap</l>
<l>            pūṇmali neṭuntērp puravi tāṅkit</l>
<l>            tāṉam maṇaṅkuta laṟiyā ṉammiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟāṉaṇaṅ kuṟṟamai kūṟik kāṉaṟ </l>
<l>            curumpimir cuṭarnuta ṉōkkip</l>
<l>            peruṅkaṭaṟ cērppaṉ ṟoḻutuniṉ ṟatuvē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>A smile came of it, friend,</l>
<l>[he] standing in worship, the man from the coast of the great sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">looking at [my] glowing forehead where bees hum</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the seashore grove,</l>
<l rend="indent3">talking of his being tormented by us,</l>
<l rend="indent">not knowing he himself is tormenting us,</l>
<l rend="indent">stopping the horses with the long chariot abounding in ornaments,</l>
<l rend="indent4">[with the words]</l>
<l rend="indent2">“you who have snatched my sweet life away, difficult to join,</l>
<l rend="indent2">who [are] you, with clear sweet words,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with wide hips to a regular fine waist,</l>
<l rend="indent2">playing with [your] companions in the ocean with clear water,</l>
<l rend="indent2">knitting, for the bees to come to [your] sapphire-like [hair put]</l>
<l rend="indent2">into five parts,</l>
<l rend="indent2">garlands of choice flowers from the Muṇṭakam with</l>
<l rend="indent2">fitly adorning blossoms?”</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="1b">
    <l>Laughter it became, friend ...<note place="foot">The beginning can be understood in two ways (related to the two ranges of association of the word <term xml:lang="ta">nakai</term>). In the first version the message is that SHE encourages HIS approaches by smiling at him, according to the second version she just laughs at him. One could, however, argue against version b that in line 9 she admits she also has been thinking of him, but that does not necessarily mean she is prepared to admit it to him.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
